DBMS Applications:
Business Information: Sales, Marketing, Human Resources, Manufacturing, Online Sellers.
Finance: Keeps records of sales and insurance and purchases of securities and bonds.
Contact: Copayment and medical bills.


Disadvantages of DBMS:
Complexity: DBMS can be difficult to install and maintain, requiring special knowledge and skills.
level. It is very high, especially for large or complex systems.
Provide storage services.


Various types of DBMS
Relational DBMS (RDBMS): RDBMS stores data in tables with rows and columns and uses SQL (Structured Query Language) to manage the data.
OODBMS stores data as objects and can be manipulated using functional expressions.
NoSQL DBMS: A NoSQL DBMS stores data in non-relational data structures, such as key-value pairs, document-based models, or graph models.

